{"article_id":"TxO7x4cJKI44nig4","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"'The solutions to these problems are hard ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"but there are solutions , '","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"Obama says .","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"|","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"REUTERS","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"Obama clarifies :","depth":3},{"id":6,"text":"Economy not fine","depth":3},{"id":7,"text":"President Barack Obama meant to shore up his economic standing with his press conference Friday ,","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"but he ended up in fast retreat .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"Obama ' s comment","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"-that \" the private sector is doing fine \" -","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"immediately became a flashpoint for Mitt Romney and congressional Republicans ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"who quickly attacked the president","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"for being out of touch about the state of the economy .","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"Within hours , he was backtracking ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"telling reporters","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"gathered in the Oval Office for a photo spray for his meeting with the president of the Philippines","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"that \" it is absolutely clear the economy is not doing fine . \"","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"Obama ' s underlying point was that private-sector job growth is outpacing austerity-sapped public payrolls ,","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"but the notion","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"that the economy is \" fine \"","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"contradicts the consensus of economists","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"who say","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"this is the weakest recovery from a recession in modern American history .","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"And it plays into the central Mitt Romney talking point :","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"That Obama is a European-style socialist hopelessly out-of-touch with the free enterprise system .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"Plus , it provides a bookend to Romney ' s own big gaffe on the economy , his off-key declaration","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"that \" corporations are people. \"","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"That didn ' t stop Romney and other Republicans from pouncing .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"\" For the president of the United States to stand up","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"and say","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"the private sector is doing fine","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"is going to go down in history as an extraordinary miscalculation and misunderstanding by a president","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"who ' s out of touch , \"","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"Romney said at a midday rally in Iowa .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"\" Are you kidding ? \"","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"asked House Majority Leader Eric Cantor","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"( R-Va. ) ,","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"speaking at a press conference","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"to rebut the president ' s remarks .","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"\" Mr . President , take it from me ,","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"the private sector is not doing well , \"","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"House Speaker John Boehner","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"( R-Ohio )","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"said at a press conference","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"soon after Obama spoke .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"And Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"( R-Ky. )","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"told Fox News ,","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"\" The president must be on another planet . \"","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"\" To argue that the private sector is in good shape ,","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"it seems to me ,","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"the president is completely disconnected from reality , \"","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"McConnell said .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"In his afternoon remarks , Obama decried the \" political games \"","depth":5},{"id":55,"text":"that had pumped up his morning comments into controversy .","depth":5},{"id":56,"text":"Obama described his comments earlier as matching what he ' s said for the last year :","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"\" we ' ve actually seen some good momentum in the private sector .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"That has not been the biggest drag on the economy . \"","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"Obama stressed","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"that he ' s aware of the economy ' s weakness ,","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"it ' s \" the reason","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"I had a press conference .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"That ' s why I spent yesterday , the day before yesterday , this past week , this past month and this past year","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"talking about how we can make the economy stronger .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"The economy is not doing fine .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"There are too many people out of work .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"The housing market is still weak ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"too many homes underwater","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"and that ' s precisely why I asked Congress to start taking some steps","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"that can make a difference . \"","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"Obama had intended his appearance in the White House briefing room to offered assurances","depth":4},{"id":73,"text":"that he ' s working to stanch Europe ' s economic troubles","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"while still pushing for growth at home .","depth":5},{"id":75,"text":"He also used his half-hour at the podium","depth":4},{"id":76,"text":"to denounce rumors","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"that leaks of key national security information had come from the White House","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"as \" offensive . \"","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":157,"left":85,"right":156,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":85,"left":83,"right":84,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":83,"left":81,"right":82,"relation":"attribution","nucleari